WEBVTT

00:07.382 --> 00:10.552
THIS IS MY HOMELAND --

00:10.594 --> 00:12.387
WADATA.

00:12.429 --> 00:13.639
YOU MAY NOT HAVE HEARD OF IT,

00:13.681 --> 00:15.182
BUT YOU WILL.

00:15.223 --> 00:17.977
WE ARE RICH IN RESOURCES,

00:18.018 --> 00:20.061
DIAMONDS,

00:20.103 --> 00:23.816
AND A NEWLY DISCOVERED

00:20.103 --> 00:23.816
OIL FIELD OFFSHORE.

00:23.858 --> 00:26.610
BUT WHILE WE ARE RICH

00:23.858 --> 00:26.610
IN RESOURCES,

00:26.652 --> 00:28.612
WE ARE POOR IN LEADERSHIP.

00:28.654 --> 00:31.866
MY BROTHER, THE PRESIDENT,

00:28.654 --> 00:31.866
IS A GOOD MAN,

00:31.907 --> 00:36.411
BUT HE DOES NOT HAVE THE WILL

00:31.907 --> 00:36.411
TO MAKE OUR COUNTRY ATTRACTIVE

00:36.453 --> 00:37.955
-TO INVESTORS.

00:36.453 --> 00:37.955
-HMM.

00:37.997 --> 00:39.247
I  DO.

00:39.289 --> 00:43.168
MR. MOTO, YOUR BROTHER

00:39.289 --> 00:43.168
IS A VERY POPULAR LEADER.

00:43.210 --> 00:46.797
HOW CONFIDENT ARE YOU

00:43.210 --> 00:46.797
THAT  YOU  CAN SUCCEED  HIM?

00:46.839 --> 00:50.049
-WELL, SOME HAVE TRIED

00:46.839 --> 00:50.049
TO STOP OUR PROGRESS...

00:46.839 --> 00:50.049
-HMM.

00:50.091 --> 00:52.302
...BUT WE ARE MAKING

00:50.091 --> 00:52.302
EVERY EFFORT

00:52.344 --> 00:54.805
-TO RESOLVE THESE CONFLICTS.

00:52.344 --> 00:54.805
-MM.

00:54.847 --> 00:58.183
[ African accent ] YOU TELL

00:54.847 --> 00:58.183
MR. MOTO THAT JANE AKINYEMI

00:58.225 --> 01:01.854
FROM THE  WEST AFRICA NEWSWIRE

00:58.225 --> 01:01.854
CALLED -- AGAIN.

01:08.903 --> 01:10.863
WAIT, THIS IS NOT FOR MY CAR.

01:10.905 --> 01:12.197
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

01:15.242 --> 01:16.326
[ GASPS ]

01:19.287 --> 01:21.206
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

01:21.248 --> 01:24.001
THE RICH AND POWERFUL

01:21.248 --> 01:24.001
TAKE WHAT THEY WANT.

01:24.043 --> 01:26.045
WE STEAL IT BACK FOR YOU.

01:32.843 --> 01:36.972
SOMETIMES, BAD GUYS

01:32.843 --> 01:36.972
MAKE THE BEST GOOD GUYS.

01:38.682 --> 01:39.934
WE PROVIDE...

01:43.854 --> 01:45.188
DAMN IT, HARDISON.

01:45.230 --> 01:46.314
WHAT ARE  YOU  DOING HERE?

01:46.356 --> 01:47.566
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,

01:46.356 --> 01:47.566
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

01:47.608 --> 01:49.234
NATE ASKED ME TO COME

01:47.608 --> 01:49.234
TO THE CLIENT MEETING

01:49.276 --> 01:50.652
'CAUSE SOMEBODY

01:49.276 --> 01:50.652
TRIED TO KILL HER.

01:50.694 --> 01:52.487
WHAT ARE  YOU  DOING HERE?

01:52.529 --> 01:55.074
I THOUGHT "TAKE YOUR DAUGHTER

01:52.529 --> 01:55.074
TO WORK" DAY WAS  LAST  WEEK.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.491
I'M HERE TO CHECK OUT

01:55.115 --> 01:56.491
WHAT NATE DOES

01:56.533 --> 01:57.910
FOR WHEN I RUN

01:56.533 --> 01:57.910
MY OWN CREW ONE DAY.

01:57.952 --> 01:59.828
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

01:57.952 --> 01:59.828
HEY, WHOA.

01:59.870 --> 02:02.581
HARDISON, THAT'S WHY

01:59.870 --> 02:02.581
YOU WANTED TO COME? NO.

02:02.623 --> 02:03.749
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "NO"?

02:03.791 --> 02:04.750
I AM THE SUPER-SKRULL.

02:04.792 --> 02:06.251
OKAY, I HAVE ALL Y'ALL'S SKILLS.

02:06.293 --> 02:07.419
I HACK, I GRIFT, I THIEVE.

02:07.461 --> 02:08.670
DO YOU FIGHT?

02:08.712 --> 02:11.590
I HAVE A DOG FOR THAT.

02:08.712 --> 02:11.590
NAME'S MEGABITE.

02:11.632 --> 02:14.175
HEY, HARDISON.

02:11.632 --> 02:14.175
YOU CAN'T DO WHAT I DO.

02:14.217 --> 02:15.886
WHY, YOU THINK

02:14.217 --> 02:15.886
I'M NOT SMART ENOUGH?

02:15.928 --> 02:17.888
NAH. NO, YOU'RE SMART ENOUGH.

02:15.928 --> 02:17.888
THAT'S THE  EASY  PART.

02:17.930 --> 02:19.306
WHAT'S THE  HARD  PART?

02:19.347 --> 02:20.766
JANE.

02:20.808 --> 02:22.935
-HELLO. YES.

02:20.808 --> 02:22.935
-NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

02:22.977 --> 02:24.394
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET

02:22.977 --> 02:24.394
MY ASSOCIATES HERE,

02:24.436 --> 02:25.604
ELIOT SPENCER

02:24.436 --> 02:25.604
AND ALEC HARDISON.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.314
PLEASE.

02:27.355 --> 02:28.690
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

02:28.732 --> 02:31.485
THOSE MEN HAVE BEEN

02:28.732 --> 02:31.485
FOLLOWING ME.

02:41.328 --> 02:43.163
[ Slurring ]

02:41.328 --> 02:43.163
SAY, MAN, I THINK --

02:43.204 --> 02:46.000
I THINK THAT'S MY JACKET

02:43.204 --> 02:46.000
THAT YOU GOT ON.

02:46.041 --> 02:47.626
[ African accent ]

02:46.041 --> 02:47.626
BACK OFF.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.962
LOOK, I LEFT IT TOO LONG

02:47.668 --> 02:49.962
AT THE DRY CLEANERS.

02:50.004 --> 02:51.839
YOU CAN'T JUST GIVE AWAY

02:50.004 --> 02:51.839
SOMEBODY'S JACKET.

02:51.880 --> 02:52.965
THIS IS MY JACKET.

02:53.007 --> 02:54.967
IF I COULD JUST GET IT BACK

02:53.007 --> 02:54.967
FROM YOU.

02:55.009 --> 02:57.052
YEAH, I LIKED IT.

02:55.009 --> 02:57.052
MY MOM GAVE IT TO ME.

02:58.012 --> 02:58.971
[ CROWD MURMURS ]

02:59.013 --> 03:01.306
-[ GROANS ]

02:59.013 --> 03:01.306
-I SAID, "BACK OFF."

03:01.348 --> 03:04.476
[ BONES CRUNCHING ]

03:01.348 --> 03:04.476
-[ GROANING ]

03:07.186 --> 03:09.106
OH!

03:09.148 --> 03:10.065
WHAT'S UP?

03:17.906 --> 03:20.034
EXCUSE ME.

03:20.075 --> 03:21.118
THANK YOU.

03:22.661 --> 03:24.496
[ BONES CRACK ]

03:24.538 --> 03:26.623
[ GRUNTS ]

03:33.964 --> 03:35.674
[ SIGHS ]

03:35.716 --> 03:38.010
CAN YOUR DOG DO THAT?

03:39.678 --> 03:42.514
THE CONDITIONS THERE

03:39.678 --> 03:42.514
ARE DEPLORABLE.

03:42.556 --> 03:45.059
WHEN THE CHILDREN WHO WORK

03:42.556 --> 03:45.059
IN MR. MOTO'S DIAMOND MINE

03:45.100 --> 03:48.687
MEET THEIR QUOTA,

03:45.100 --> 03:48.687
THEY EARN $1.50 A DAY.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.814
WHEN THEY DON'T, THEY GO HUNGRY.

03:50.856 --> 03:53.608
YEAH, OR WORSE.

03:55.069 --> 03:56.945
I'VE FOUGHT IN THESE COUNTRIES.

03:56.987 --> 03:58.197
I'VE SEEN THESE KIDS.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.573
YOU MAKE IT OUT OF THE MINE,

03:59.614 --> 04:02.409
WELL, THEN YOU GET AN M-16

03:59.614 --> 04:02.409
IN THE REBEL ARMY.

04:02.450 --> 04:05.662
AND MR. MOTO, HE SMUGGLES

04:02.450 --> 04:05.662
HIS DIAMONDS INTO THE U.S.,

04:05.704 --> 04:07.706
AND THEN HE LAUNDERS THEM

04:05.704 --> 04:07.706
THROUGH HIS REAL-ESTATE HOLDINGS

04:07.748 --> 04:09.083
HERE IN BOSTON.

04:09.124 --> 04:10.834
I GUESS IT PAYS TO HAVE

04:09.124 --> 04:10.834
A BROTHER WHO'S PRESIDENT.

04:10.876 --> 04:12.544
THE PRESIDENT IS A GOOD MAN

04:12.586 --> 04:14.963
WHO HAS WORKED HARD

04:12.586 --> 04:14.963
TO RAISE THE STANDARD OF LIVING

04:15.005 --> 04:16.464
FOR OUR PEOPLE.

04:16.506 --> 04:18.800
BUT HIS BROTHER IS VERY SMART.

04:18.842 --> 04:20.969
HE COVERS HIS TRACKS.

04:21.011 --> 04:22.512
THAT IS WHY HE'LL WIN.

04:22.554 --> 04:24.681
THIS MONEY

04:22.554 --> 04:24.681
THAT ALEXANDER'S SAVING --

04:24.723 --> 04:25.849
THIS -- THIS IS FOR A COUP?

04:25.891 --> 04:27.392
NO. AN ELECTION.

04:27.434 --> 04:30.729
TERM LIMITS WILL FORCE HIS

04:27.434 --> 04:30.729
BROTHER OUT IN LESS THAN A YEAR.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.731
NOTHING WILL STOP

04:30.771 --> 04:32.731
ALEXANDER THEN.

04:32.773 --> 04:36.193
RUMOR HAS IT HE'S ALREADY SOLD

04:32.773 --> 04:36.193
THE COUNTRY TO CORPORATIONS.

04:36.235 --> 04:38.904
YEAH, FOR THAT GIANT OIL FIELD

04:36.235 --> 04:38.904
THEY DISCOVERED, RIGHT?

04:38.946 --> 04:41.322
SO, FROM DIAMOND SMUGGLER

04:38.946 --> 04:41.322
TO OPEC MEMBER.

04:41.364 --> 04:42.574
THAT'S A NICE BOUNCE.

04:42.616 --> 04:43.951
IN FOUR DAYS,

04:43.992 --> 04:46.620
OUR PRESIDENT WILL VISIT

04:43.992 --> 04:46.620
HIS BROTHER HERE IN BOSTON.

04:46.661 --> 04:48.538
THAT WILL SOLIDIFY ALEXANDER

04:48.580 --> 04:50.207
AS HIS HEIR APPARENT BACK HOME.

04:50.249 --> 04:51.708
JANE,

04:50.249 --> 04:51.708
DON'T YOU THINK THAT WHEN --

04:51.750 --> 04:53.168
WHEN THAT ARTICLE

04:51.750 --> 04:53.168
YOU WROTE COMES OUT,

04:53.210 --> 04:54.419
THAT THE JUSTICE DEPARTMENT --

04:54.461 --> 04:55.754
WILL DO NOTHING!

04:55.796 --> 04:58.257
I BROUGHT THEM PROOF

04:55.796 --> 04:58.257
OF MOTO'S CRIMES MONTHS AGO.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.759
THEY STARTED AN INVESTIGATION,

04:58.298 --> 05:00.759
THEN STOPPED.

05:00.801 --> 05:01.802
WHY?

05:01.843 --> 05:04.304
I DON'T KNOW.

05:04.345 --> 05:06.932
BUT I KNOW HOW TO FIND OUT.

05:18.318 --> 05:21.655
WELL, THANK YOU FOR SEEING ME

05:18.318 --> 05:21.655
ON, UH, SHORT NOTICE.

05:21.696 --> 05:23.740
YOU ARE HELPING ME

05:21.696 --> 05:23.740
TO CATCH DAMIEN MOREAU.

05:23.782 --> 05:25.867
IT'S JUST GOOD MANNERS.

05:25.909 --> 05:27.244
DID I DRAG YOU AWAY

05:25.909 --> 05:27.244
FROM A-A PARTY OR SOMETHING?

05:27.286 --> 05:30.038
A DATE...WITH A FUGITIVE...

05:30.080 --> 05:31.665
WHO IS NO LONGER A FUGITIVE.

05:31.706 --> 05:32.833
OH.

05:34.042 --> 05:35.085
OH.

05:35.127 --> 05:37.087
MR. FORD,

05:35.127 --> 05:37.087
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.

05:37.129 --> 05:39.338
YOU COME HERE

05:37.129 --> 05:39.338
ABOUT ALEXANDER MOTO, RIGHT?

05:39.380 --> 05:40.465
YES, YES, YES.

05:40.507 --> 05:42.634
DIAMOND SMUGGLER,

05:40.507 --> 05:42.634
ASPIRING KLEPTOCRAT --

05:42.676 --> 05:44.719
SEEMED LIKE, UH,

05:42.676 --> 05:44.719
YOUR KIND OF GUY.

05:44.761 --> 05:47.430
YOU WANTED TO KNOW WHY

05:44.761 --> 05:47.430
THE U.S. LEAVES HIM ALONE?

05:47.472 --> 05:48.556
THAT'S RIGHT.

05:48.598 --> 05:49.599
HERE IT IS.

05:49.641 --> 05:51.977
HE IDENTIFIES JIHADISTS

05:49.641 --> 05:51.977
IN AFRICA.

05:52.019 --> 05:53.352
YOU MEAN TERRORISTS.

05:53.394 --> 05:54.521
HE'S A PAID INFORMANT.

05:54.562 --> 05:55.689
YES.

05:55.730 --> 05:57.274
ONCE A MONTH,

05:55.730 --> 05:57.274
HE GIVES C.I.A. A NAME,

05:57.316 --> 05:59.818
-AND THEY GIVE HIM BACK MONEY.

05:57.316 --> 05:59.818
-MM-HMM.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.569
IT'S [SIGHS]

06:01.611 --> 06:03.571
COME SI DICE?

06:03.613 --> 06:04.656
A SIDE JOB?

06:06.992 --> 06:08.118
HAVE YOU HAD DINNER?

06:09.328 --> 06:11.288
'CAUSE I DON'T LIKE

06:09.328 --> 06:11.288
EATING ALONE.

06:13.290 --> 06:14.624
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

06:16.210 --> 06:20.005
[ GAGGING ]

06:23.466 --> 06:25.552
Y-YEAH, I GOT PLANS.

06:25.593 --> 06:27.346
WELL...

06:27.386 --> 06:29.139
IT WILL BE FOR THE NEXT TIME.

06:29.181 --> 06:30.765
YEAH, 'CAUSE...

06:34.686 --> 06:35.937
WAIT A MINUTE.

06:35.979 --> 06:37.689
THIS GUY MAKES MONEY

06:35.979 --> 06:37.689
OFF THE BACKS OF CHILDREN,

06:37.731 --> 06:38.940
AND NOBODY GOES AFTER HIM

06:38.982 --> 06:41.151
BECAUSE HE FEEDS THE C.I.A.

06:38.982 --> 06:41.151
A BUNCH OF NAMES?

06:41.193 --> 06:43.486
AND WHAT ARE THE ODDS THAT

06:41.193 --> 06:43.486
THESE CO-CALLED "JIHADISTS"

06:43.528 --> 06:45.030
AREN'T TERRORISTS AT ALL?

06:45.072 --> 06:47.991
THEY'RE MORE LIKELY TO BE MOTO'S

06:45.072 --> 06:47.991
POLITICAL RIVALS BACK HOME.

06:48.033 --> 06:49.826
I'LL TAKE THAT BET.

06:49.868 --> 06:52.037
AND IF THE GOVERNMENT

06:49.868 --> 06:52.037
WON'T GO AFTER MOTO, WE WILL.

06:52.079 --> 06:54.748
NOW, HE BOUGHT HIS REAL ESTATE

06:52.079 --> 06:54.748
AT THE TOP OF THE MARKET,

06:54.789 --> 06:56.708
SO HE'S LEVERAGED

06:54.789 --> 06:56.708
UP TO HIS EYEBALLS.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.336
AND THE ONLY THING KEEPING HIM

06:56.750 --> 06:59.336
AFLOAT FROM NOT GOING BANKRUPT

06:59.378 --> 07:00.837
IS THE STEADY FLOW OF DIAMONDS.

07:00.879 --> 07:02.714
AND WHAT'S THE BEST THING

07:00.879 --> 07:02.714
ABOUT SMUGGLED DIAMONDS?

07:02.756 --> 07:04.007
OH, I KNOW THIS ONE.

07:04.049 --> 07:05.550
IT'S THE WAY THAT THEY SHIMMER

07:05.592 --> 07:07.635
ON THE DECK

07:05.592 --> 07:07.635
OF A BILLIONAIRE'S YACHT

07:07.677 --> 07:09.512
IN THE MOONLIGHT.

07:10.972 --> 07:13.058
BECAUSE THEY'RE UNINSURED.

07:13.100 --> 07:14.101
RIGHT.

07:14.142 --> 07:17.145
SO, WE GO AFTER MOTO'S DIAMONDS,

07:17.187 --> 07:21.275
AND WE END A POLITICAL CAREER

07:17.187 --> 07:21.275
BEFORE IT STARTS.

07:21.316 --> 07:23.568
WE JUST HAVE TO FIND OUT

07:21.316 --> 07:23.568
WHERE THE VAULT IS.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.070
-Parker.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.070
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

07:25.112 --> 07:27.948
OKAY, WE ARE AT STOP 4

07:25.112 --> 07:27.948
ON OUR TOUR

07:27.989 --> 07:31.118
OF ALEXANDER MOTO'S

07:27.989 --> 07:31.118
BOSTON PROPERTIES.

07:33.287 --> 07:34.579
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

07:34.621 --> 07:36.539
RECORDS SHOW

07:34.621 --> 07:36.539
HE JUST RENOVATED THE PLACE

07:36.581 --> 07:38.458
WITH STATE-OF-THE-ART

07:36.581 --> 07:38.458
SECURITY TECH,

07:38.499 --> 07:40.294
BUT HE WOULDN'T PUT A VAULT

07:38.499 --> 07:40.294
IN HERE.

07:40.335 --> 07:41.211
Why is that?

07:41.253 --> 07:42.879
IT'S RAINES CONCERT HALL,

07:42.921 --> 07:45.382
WHERE THE MASSACHUSETTS

07:42.921 --> 07:45.382
CHAMBER ORCHESTRA PLAYS. WHY --

07:45.424 --> 07:46.925
THEY HAVE CONCERTS HERE?

07:46.967 --> 07:48.927
LOOK AT THAT FOUNDATION.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.220
I THOUGHT THIS WAS A BANK.

07:50.262 --> 07:51.596
Like -- Like I said --

07:51.638 --> 07:53.390
IT'S THE  PERFECT  PLACE

07:51.638 --> 07:53.390
FOR A VAULT.

07:53.432 --> 07:54.766
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:54.808 --> 07:55.850
AWW.

07:55.892 --> 07:57.685
JUNIOR HIGH.

07:57.727 --> 08:01.398
AND THEY THOUGHT JACKIE THOMAS'

07:57.727 --> 08:01.398
REPORT CARD WAS SAFE.

08:03.733 --> 08:05.610
GUYS, THEY HAVE

08:03.733 --> 08:05.610
A DEDICATED AIR LINE

08:05.652 --> 08:08.447
THAT GOES STRAIGHT DOWN

08:05.652 --> 08:08.447
TO THE BASEMENT.

08:08.488 --> 08:12.700
USED FOR STORING

08:08.488 --> 08:12.700
EXTREMELY  DELICATE ITEMS.

08:12.742 --> 08:15.120
THAT'S WHERE YOUR VAULT IS.

08:15.162 --> 08:18.415
HEY, GUYS, I  THINK  I MAY HAVE

08:15.162 --> 08:18.415
FOUND HIS FRAGILE ITEM.

08:18.457 --> 08:21.668
MOTO JUST PURCHASED

08:18.457 --> 08:21.668
A STRADIVARIUS VIOLIN

08:21.709 --> 08:24.921
FOR $4.5 MILLION.

08:24.963 --> 08:26.506
THIS ALL FITS.

08:26.547 --> 08:29.426
MOTO'S MADE HIMSELF A PATRON

08:26.547 --> 08:29.426
OF THE ARTS IN BOSTON

08:29.468 --> 08:32.512
TO, YOU KNOW, UP HIS PROFILE

08:29.468 --> 08:32.512
WITH THE OLD-MONEY CROWD.

08:32.553 --> 08:34.139
AND WHAT'S HIS VULNERABILITY?

08:34.181 --> 08:35.640
HIS TIES TO AMERICA.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.809
HIS FATHER SENT HIM OUT

08:35.682 --> 08:37.809
OF THE COUNTRY AT AN EARLY AGE.

08:37.851 --> 08:40.812
HE WAS EDUCATED IN EUROPE,

08:37.851 --> 08:40.812
GOT HIS MBA AT HARVARD.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.605
HIS BROTHER'S A NATIONAL HERO.

08:42.647 --> 08:44.983
BUT MOTO DOESN'T EVEN SPEAK

08:42.647 --> 08:44.983
HIS NATIVE LANGUAGE.

08:45.025 --> 08:47.486
HE'S GONNA HAVE TO KISS

08:45.025 --> 08:47.486
A  LOT  OF BABIES...

08:47.527 --> 08:50.613
OR STUFF A LOT OF BALLOT BOXES.

08:50.655 --> 08:52.324
SO MOTO'S PROBLEM IS,

08:52.366 --> 08:54.575
IS THAT HE'S AN OUTSIDER

08:52.366 --> 08:54.575
TO HIS OWN PEOPLE.

08:54.617 --> 08:56.786
Yeah, well,

08:54.617 --> 08:56.786
what about  my  problem?

08:56.828 --> 09:00.165
I CAN'T BREAK INTO A VAULT

08:56.828 --> 09:00.165
WITHOUT SEEING THE INSIDE FIRST.

09:00.207 --> 09:03.377
YEAH, OKAY, SO,

09:00.207 --> 09:03.377
YOU NEED A TOUR OF THE VAULT,

09:03.418 --> 09:07.547
AND MOTO, OUR MARK,

09:03.418 --> 09:07.547
NEEDS TO LOOK GOOD BACK HOME.

09:09.341 --> 09:12.010
LET'S GO STEAL

09:09.341 --> 09:12.010
THE MAN ON THE STREET.

09:13.011 --> 09:15.055
IN AFRICA.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.605
JANE, HAS MOTO

09:22.729 --> 09:24.605
EVER GIVEN YOU AN INTERVIEW?

09:24.647 --> 09:26.233
-Never.

09:24.647 --> 09:26.233
-DOES HE DRINK?

09:26.274 --> 09:27.692
ON OCCASION. WHY?

09:27.734 --> 09:29.403
NO REASON.

09:29.444 --> 09:31.196
LISTEN,

09:29.444 --> 09:31.196
STAY AWAY FROM YOUR APARTMENT,

09:31.238 --> 09:33.656
AND CALL ME AT THE FIRST SIGN

09:31.238 --> 09:33.656
OF ANY TROUBLE.

09:33.698 --> 09:34.574
OKAY.

09:38.286 --> 09:41.748
THAT'S NICE. MAKE HIM --

09:38.286 --> 09:41.748
MAKE HIM LOOK DRUNKER.

09:41.789 --> 09:43.083
AND THEN RICHER.

09:43.124 --> 09:45.585
WHAT YOU WANT ME TO DO,

09:43.124 --> 09:45.585
GIVE THE MAN A PET TIGER?

09:45.626 --> 09:47.421
CAN YOU DO THAT?

09:57.431 --> 09:59.433
THE PROTESTS WERE SPARKED

09:57.431 --> 09:59.433
BY AN INTERVIEW

09:59.474 --> 10:00.934
WITH THE PRESIDENT'S BROTHER

10:00.975 --> 10:03.603
IN WHICH HE REFERRED TO

10:00.975 --> 10:03.603
THE WADATA NATIONAL SOCCER TEAM

10:03.644 --> 10:05.813
AS..."LITTLE SCHOOLGIRLS."

10:05.855 --> 10:07.107
IN ANY --

10:07.148 --> 10:08.275
WHOA.

10:08.316 --> 10:09.692
THAT WAS A CLOSE ONE.

